      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IT'S A TEASE (4) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 1.3 lengths at this track in a handy 29.66 beating FASCINATE BAILEY. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Has put together a string of wins and expected to go close again. FASCINATE BAILEY (7) stalked the lead after a clean break from the tricky draw and went on to finish second (29.75) at this track in a Grade 5 over 515m. Expecting another good run. HANK MCCOY (6) last start finished 2nd over 400m at Maitland beaten 2.75 lengths (22.82) behind Red Opal in a Grade 4/5 on March 9. Looks one of the chances. JONESY REVENGE (2) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
